<paragraph id="1019E25DA539FFE4FF07FA3FFDE07599" blockId="17.[136,575,1415,1442]" box="[136,575,1415,1442]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">
<heading id="4B515531A539FFE4FF07FA3FFDE07599" bold="true" box="[136,575,1415,1442]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" reason="1">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FF07FA3FFDE07599" bold="true" box="[136,575,1415,1442]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">
Variation in 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA539FFE4FE91FA3FFDE07599" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[286,575,1415,1442]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FE91FA3FFDE07599" bold="true" box="[286,575,1415,1442]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Cryptantha echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA539FFE4FF07FA68FEB2774E" blockId="17.[136,1452,1487,1909]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">
In our study of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA539FFE4FEB9FA77FD8E75D2" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[310,593,1487,1513]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FEB9FA77FD8E75D2" box="[310,593,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Cryptantha echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we noted two disjunct regions of distribution, one in the islands adjacent to Magdalena Bay on the Pacific Ocean side of the 
<collectingRegion id="D2622CBFA539FFE4FD22FA4BFC857636" box="[685,858,1523,1549]" country="Mexico" name="Baja California" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Baja California</collectingRegion>
peninsula, and one in the Sierra de La Giganta, Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="D2622CBFA539FFE4FF29F9AFFEC7760A" box="[166,280,1559,1585]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">California</collectingRegion>
coastal regions, and northeastern 
<collectingRegion id="D2622CBFA539FFE4FD1DF9AFFCC5760A" box="[658,794,1559,1585]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Cape region</collectingRegion>
of the peninsula (
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A539FFE4FC6FF9AFFBEC760A" box="[992,1075,1559,1585]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1275,1297]" captionTargetBox="[152,1433,190,1248]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[152,1436,190,1250]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cryptantha echinosepala [Johnstonella e.] distribution maps, coordinates from Baja Flora (2021).A. Topography map. Map from ©Google 2020, INEGI Data. B. Map from Baja Flora (2021) showing vegetation zones (after Rebman et al. 2016) where the species occurs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426156/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). These two regions are separated by the extensive Magdalena Plains (
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A539FFE4FDA4F983FD4A766E" box="[555,661,1595,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1275,1297]" captionTargetBox="[152,1433,190,1248]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[152,1436,190,1250]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cryptantha echinosepala [Johnstonella e.] distribution maps, coordinates from Baja Flora (2021).A. Topography map. Map from ©Google 2020, INEGI Data. B. Map from Baja Flora (2021) showing vegetation zones (after Rebman et al. 2016) where the species occurs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426156/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). A comparison of specimens from these two regions revealed some morphological differences. Plants from Magdalena Island, the 
<typeStatus id="CF1D5CFFA539FFE4FCC2F9D8FCA27641" box="[845,893,1632,1658]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA539FFE4FB8DF9D8FB677642" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[1026,1208,1631,1658]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FB8DF9D8FB677642" box="[1026,1208,1631,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">C. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tend to have cauline leaves lacking strong bristle-like trichomes on the margins, shorter inflorescences with the flowers more clustered, and possibly smaller calyces. Plants from the Sierra de La Giganta near the Gulf side tend to have cauline leaves with prominent marginal setose trichomes, longer inflorescence cymules with the flowers more separated, and larger calyces. We do not think that these differences are sufficient enough to give different names to the populations of these two centers of distribution at present, pending more detailed studies. If future morphometric and/or molecular analyses show strong differences between populations of these two regions, there may be justification for separating them taxonomically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA539FFE4FF07F81BFE567780" blockId="17.[136,393,1955,1982]" box="[136,393,1955,1982]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FF07F81BFF687780" bold="true" box="[136,183,1955,1981]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">THE</emphasis>
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FF31F81CFEE77780" bold="true" box="[190,312,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">MARITIMAE</emphasis>
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FEB0F81BFE567780" bold="true" box="[319,393,1955,1981]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">CLADE</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA539FFE7FF07F853FDF57327" blockId="17.[136,1451,2027,2090]" lastBlockId="18.[136,1452,158,1121]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="203" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">
The 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FF35F854FEEF783E" box="[186,304,2028,2053]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade (after 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA539FFE4FE34F853FD72783E" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[443,685,2027,2054]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref13012" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1925) Studies in the Boraginaceae IV. The North American species of Cryptantha. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 74: 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1925">Johnston’s (1925: 44)</bibRefCitation>
series 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FD76F854FCB0783E" box="[761,879,2028,2053]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">Maritimae</emphasis>
) refers to a monophyletic group named in 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA539FFE4FAC6F853FEC37812" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Guilliams, C. M. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L." pageId="17" pageNumber="202" pagination="1406 - 1420" refId="ref14215" refString="Simpson, M. G., Guilliams, C. M., Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L. (2017 a) Phylogeny of the popcorn flowers: Use of genome skimming to evaluate monophyly and interrelationships in subtribe Amsinckiinae (Boraginaceae). Taxon 66: 1406 - 1420. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA539FFE4FF07F7A8FF607812" box="[136,191,2063,2089]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="202">et al.</emphasis>
(2017a)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA539FFE4FEDEF7B7FDAC7812" author="Mabry, M. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G." box="[337,627,2063,2089]" pageId="17" pageNumber="202" pagination="53 - 76" refId="ref13462" refString="Mabry, M. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G. (2018) Evaluating the monophyly and biogeography of Cryptantha (Boraginaceae). Systematic Botany 43: 53 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 696978" type="journal article" year="2018">Mabry &amp; Simpson (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. This clade was well-supported from molecular data and separate from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF5FFF26FE8F7083" box="[208,336,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF5FFF26FE8F7083" box="[208,336,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although its placement within the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FCB6FF26FC0A7083" authorityName="Brand" authorityYear="1931" box="[825,981,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Amsinckiinae">Amsinckiinae</taxonomicName>
varied depending on the 
<typeStatus id="CF1D5CFFA53AFFE7FB60FF27FAC07082" box="[1263,1311,159,185]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">type</typeStatus>
of sequence data analyzed. 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FEBDFF7AFD0C70E7" author="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G." box="[306,723,194,220]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="738 - 757" refId="ref12746" refString="Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Simpson, M. G. (2012) Cat's eyes and popcorn flowers: Phylogenetic systematics of the genus Cryptantha s. l. (Boraginaceae). Systematic Botany 37: 738 - 757. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364412 X 648706" type="journal article" year="2012">Hasenstab-Lehman &amp; Simpson 2012</bibRefCitation>
first discovered that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FBB5FF7AFB6570E7" box="[1082,1210,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FBB5FF7AFB6570E7" box="[1082,1210,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FB4DFF7AFB3C70E7" box="[1218,1251,194,220]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was polyphyletic and best separated into six groups: the genera 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FD2FFF5FFC01713B" box="[672,990,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FD2FFF5FFCF3713B" box="[672,812,231,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eremocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Eremocarya</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FCB6FF5EFC01713B" box="[825,990,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Greeneocharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Greeneocharis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC60FF5EFB5A713B" box="[1007,1157,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC60FF5EFB5E713B" box="[1007,1153,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Johnstonella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FB4EFF5FFA9F713A" box="[1217,1344,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FB4EFF5FFAE3713A" box="[1217,1340,231,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Oreocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Oreocarya</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
plus two other clades: a large one (termed 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FD9AFEB2FD4A711F" box="[533,661,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FD9AFEB2FD4A711F" box="[533,661,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FD2FFEB2FD1B711F" box="[672,708,266,292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
1) containing the bulk of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC7BFEB2FB10711F" box="[1012,1231,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC7BFEB2FBAB711F" box="[1012,1140,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
and a smaller one (termed 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF66FE96FEB67173" box="[233,361,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF66FE96FEB67173" box="[233,361,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FEFCFE96FE4C7173" box="[371,403,302,328]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
2), containing the North and South American 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC23FE96FB427173" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[940,1181,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC23FE96FB427173" box="[940,1181,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FB63FE97FAA87173" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1260,1399,303,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FB63FE97FAA87173" box="[1260,1399,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF07FEEBFF7B7157" box="[136,164,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">m.</emphasis>
of North America and a South American specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC80FEEBFBC97157" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1922" box="[783,1046,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="pilosa">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC80FEEBFC487157" box="[783,919,339,365]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. maritima</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC5DFEEAFBC97157" box="[978,1046,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sampled) plus two South American species: 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF66FECFFC5F71AA" authority="(Ruiz &amp; Pavon 1799: 5) Johnston (1923: 54)" authorityName="Johnston" authorityPageNumber="54" authorityYear="1923" baseAuthorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" baseAuthorityPageNumber="5" baseAuthorityYear="1799" box="[233,896,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF66FECFFEA271AB" box="[233,381,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. granulosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FE03FECEFD5371AA" author="Ruiz, H. &amp; Pavon, J." box="[396,652,374,401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" refId="ref13811" refString="Ruiz, H. &amp; Pavon, J. (1799) Flora Peruviana et Chilensis. Tomus 2: Superiorum Permissu, Typis Gabrielis de Sancha, 70 pp." type="book" year="1799">Ruiz &amp; Pavon 1799: 5</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD11FECEFC5F71AA" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[670,896,374,401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="52 - 57" refId="ref12930" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1923) Studies in the Boraginaceae. Novelties and new combinations in the genus Cryptantha. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 68: 52 - 57." type="journal article" year="1923">Johnston (1923: 54)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC36FECFFEDC718F" authority="(Philippi 1860: 39) Johnston (1927: 43)" authorityName="Johnston" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1927" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityPageNumber="39" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC36FECFFBBE71AB" box="[953,1121,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. chaetocalyx</emphasis>
(Philippi 1860: 39) 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FAC7FECEFEDC718F" author="Johnston, I. M." pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref13048" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1927) Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1927">Johnston (1927: 43)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FE80FE22FDDE718F" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Guilliams, C. M. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L." box="[271,513,410,437]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="1406 - 1420" refId="ref14215" refString="Simpson, M. G., Guilliams, C. M., Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L. (2017 a) Phylogeny of the popcorn flowers: Use of genome skimming to evaluate monophyly and interrelationships in subtribe Amsinckiinae (Boraginaceae). Taxon 66: 1406 - 1420. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FEF5FE23FE72718F" box="[378,429,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">et al</emphasis>
. 2017a
</bibRefCitation>
sampled considerably more taxa in the subtribe and obtained very similar results. This later study also retrieved the same four segregate genera and a diphyletic 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC78FE06FBA871E3" box="[1015,1143,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC78FE06FBA871E3" box="[1015,1143,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FBF2FE07FB7E71E2" box="[1149,1185,447,473]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The bulk of the species occurred in a “core” 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FEF9FE5AFE2971C7" box="[374,502,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FEF9FE5AFE2971C7" box="[374,502,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FE71FE5BFDFD71C6" box="[510,546,483,509]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
clade, this largely equivalent to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC19FE5AFBC971C7" box="[918,1046,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC19FE5AFBC971C7" box="[918,1046,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FB92FE5AFB9D71C7" box="[1053,1090,482,508]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
1 and containing the 
<typeStatus id="CF1D5CFFA53AFFE7FABEFE5BFABE71C6" box="[1329,1377,483,509]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">type</typeStatus>
of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF57FDBFFD17721B" authority="Lehmann ex Don (1837: 373)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="373" authorityYear="1837" box="[216,712,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF57FDBFFEB2721B" box="[216,365,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. glomerata</emphasis>
Lehmann ex 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD87FDBFFD17721B" author="Don, G." box="[520,712,518,545]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" refId="ref12385" refString="Don, G. (1837) A General History of the Dichlamydeous Plants (Original Title: A General System of Gardening and Botany). 4 (Corolliflorae): 1 - 908. London, UK: Gilbert &amp; Rivington." type="book" year="1837">Don (1837: 373)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A few 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC91FDBEFC25721B" box="[798,1018,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC91FDBEFC41721B" box="[798,926,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, however, occurred in a smaller clade, termed the 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE85FD93FE5F727F" box="[266,384,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade as mentioned earlier, containing taxa similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC7DFD92FBAD727F" box="[1010,1138,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC7DFD92FBAD727F" box="[1010,1138,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FBF4FD92FB42727F" box="[1147,1181,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
2. The 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FB7EFD93FAB8727F" box="[1265,1383,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade of 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FF27FDF6FE747253" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Guilliams, C. M. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L." box="[168,427,590,616]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="1406 - 1420" refId="ref14215" refString="Simpson, M. G., Guilliams, C. M., Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L. (2017 a) Phylogeny of the popcorn flowers: Use of genome skimming to evaluate monophyly and interrelationships in subtribe Amsinckiinae (Boraginaceae). Taxon 66: 1406 - 1420. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE9DFDF7FE947253" box="[274,331,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">et al.</emphasis>
(2017a)
</bibRefCitation>
consisted of the North American 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FCA3FDF6FB217253" authority="Johnston (1939: 387)" authorityName="Johnston" authorityPageNumber="387" authorityYear="1939" box="[812,1278,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="clokeyi">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FCA3FDF6FBDC7253" box="[812,1027,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha clokeyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FB84FDF6FB217253" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[1035,1278,590,616]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="375 - 402" refId="ref13122" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1939) Studies in the Boraginaceae, XIII: New or otherwise noteworthy species, chiefly from western United States. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 20: 375 - 402. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21105" type="journal article" year="1939">Johnston (1939: 387)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FA84FDF7FDF872B6" authority="M. G. Simpson &amp; Rebman (2013: 35)" authorityName="M. G. Simpson &amp; Rebman" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martirensis">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FA84FDF7FA737253" box="[1291,1452,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. martirensis</emphasis>
M.G.Simpson &amp; Rebman (2013: 35)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FDE8FDCBFEFD728B" authority="(Hooker &amp; Arnott 1840: 369) Nelson &amp; Macbride (1916: 42) var. muricata" authorityName="Nelson &amp; Macbride" authorityYear="1916" baseAuthorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="muricata" variety="muricata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FDE8FDCBFD3172B7" box="[615,750,627,653]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. muricata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD72FDCAFBE372B6" author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[765,1084,626,653]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" refId="ref12804" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1840) The Botany of Captain Beechy's Voyage. Henry G. Bohn, London, 444 pp." type="book" year="1840">Hooker &amp; Arnott 1840: 369</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FBC3FDCAFA7472B7" author="Nelson, A. &amp; Macbride, J. F." box="[1100,1451,626,652]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="30 - 47" refId="ref13544" refString="Nelson, A. &amp; Macbride, J. F. (1916) Western Plant Studies III. Botanical Gazette 61: 30 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 331713" type="journal article" year="1916">Nelson &amp; Macbride (1916: 42)</bibRefCitation>
var. 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF35FD2FFEFD728B" box="[186,290,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FEADFD2FFEF9728B" box="[290,294,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">,</emphasis>
plus a sister subclade of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FDC5FD2EFD15728B" box="[586,714,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FDC5FD2EFD15728B" box="[586,714,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FD54FD2EFCB5728B" box="[731,874,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Johnstonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FD54FD2EFCB5728B" box="[731,874,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Johnstonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FCF3FD2EFBCF728B" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[892,1040,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FCF3FD2EFBCF728B" box="[892,1040,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FBAFFD2FFB76728B" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1056,1193,663,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FBAFFD2FFB76728B" box="[1056,1193,663,689]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FB6CFD2FFB20728B" box="[1251,1279,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">m.</emphasis>
, and the South American 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FE8FFD03FC6B72EE" authority="(Philippi 1860: 39) Reiche (1907: 826)" authorityName="Reiche" authorityPageNumber="826" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityPageNumber="39" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[256,948,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subamplexicaulis">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE8FFD03FE3972EF" box="[256,486,698,725]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. subamplexicaulis</emphasis>
(Philippi 1860: 39) 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD5BFD02FC6B72EE" author="Reiche, K." box="[724,948,698,725]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="803 - 835" refId="ref13778" refString="Reiche, K. (1907) Estudios Criticos Sobre la Flora de Chile (Continuacion): Familia Borrajinaceas. Anales de la Universidad de Chile 121: 803 - 835." type="journal article" year="1907">Reiche (1907: 826)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC43FD02FB1872EF" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1923" baseAuthorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" baseAuthorityYear="1799" box="[972,1223,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC43FD02FB1872EF" box="[972,1223,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FA8DFD03FA7372EF" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1927" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1282,1452,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FA8DFD03FA7372EF" box="[1282,1452,698,725]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. chaetocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not sequenced in that study.) The 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FDC6FD67FD6072C3" box="[585,703,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade was well supported, but its relationship to other clades and genera of the subtribe was equivocal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1019E25DA53AFFE7FF32FC9EFE70745A" blockId="18.[136,1452,158,1121]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">
Of the five species placed by 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD9FFC9EFD2C737B" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[528,755,806,833]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref13012" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1925) Studies in the Boraginaceae IV. The North American species of Cryptantha. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 74: 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1925">Johnston (1925: 44)</bibRefCitation>
in his series 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC05FC9FFBDF737B" box="[906,1024,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
, only two— 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FB1FFC9EFA73737B" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[1168,1452,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FB1FFC9EFA73737B" box="[1168,1452,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF36FCF3FE83735F" box="[185,348,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF36FCF3FEE0735F" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[185,319,843,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">C. maritima</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
occurred in the 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FD9FFCF3FD59735F" box="[528,646,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade of 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA53AFFE7FD7CFCF2FC24735F" author="Simpson, M. G. &amp; Guilliams, C. M. &amp; Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E. &amp; Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L." box="[755,1019,842,869]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" pagination="1406 - 1420" refId="ref14215" refString="Simpson, M. G., Guilliams, C. M., Hasenstab-Lehman, K. E., Mabry, M. E. &amp; Ripma, L. (2017 a) Phylogeny of the popcorn flowers: Use of genome skimming to evaluate monophyly and interrelationships in subtribe Amsinckiinae (Boraginaceae). Taxon 66: 1406 - 1420. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Simpson 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FCD1FCF3FC4E735F" box="[862,913,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">et al</emphasis>
. (2017a)
</bibRefCitation>
. The other three species— 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FAA3FCF2FED773B3" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dumetorum">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FAA3FCF2FED773B3" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha dumetorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FE9BFCD7FE6B73B3" authorityName="Hasenstab &amp; Simpson" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[276,436,879,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micromeres">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE9BFCD7FE6B73B3" box="[276,436,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. micromeres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FE61FCD7FDA673B3" authorityName="Coville" authorityYear="1895" box="[494,633,879,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurvata">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE61FCD7FDA673B3" box="[494,633,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. recurvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—all group firmly within 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC1CFCD6FBCC73B3" box="[915,1043,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC1CFCD6FBCC73B3" box="[915,1043,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FB97FCD7FBE373B2" box="[1048,1084,879,905]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in their analyses. The similarities of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FF28FC2AFEA87397" authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[167,375,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF28FC2AFEA87397" box="[167,375,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FE13FC2BFDFA7397" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[412,549,915,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FE13FC2BFDFA7397" box="[412,549,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lead us to surmise that the former might also be best placed with the other taxa of the 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FF5BFC0FFE9573EB" box="[212,330,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade, including 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FD9CFC0FFD1573EB" authorityName="Macbride" authorityYear="1918" box="[531,714,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinosepala">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FD9CFC0FFD1573EB" box="[531,714,950,977]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. echinosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Future sequencing of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FC5AFC0FFB9F73EB" authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[981,1088,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FC5AFC0FFB9F73EB" box="[981,1088,950,977]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">C. pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be needed to confirm this, although it may be difficult to obtain DNA material given its extreme rarity. However, we reiterate that this 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FABAFC63FA7473CF" box="[1333,1451,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Maritimae</emphasis>
clade forms a well-supported monophyletic group in the three molecular phylogenetic studies cited, a group separate from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FEBAFB9AFE6A7407" box="[309,437,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FEBAFB9AFE6A7407" box="[309,437,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39E18334A53AFFE7FE35FB9BFE017406" box="[442,478,1059,1085]" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The members of that clade may, in fact, best be placed in a new genus in the future, one separate from 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA53AFFE7FEA7FBFEFE77745B" box="[296,424,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="18" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA53AFFE7FEA7FBFEFE77745B" box="[296,424,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="203">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
